N2  - The article discusses a study conducted by the University of California Research Institute for Business and Economics. The study analyzed the communication practices of an aerospace company in the U.S. Top managers at the aerospace firm identified communication practices at the lower organizational levels among the biggest problems as well as a lack of speed in communication, both vertically and horizontally. They also expressed concern over the lack of accuracy in communications and the need for each executive to have extensive amounts of information immediately available.
