N2  - The article outlines the role of the native enterprise manager in Alaska. Twenty seven village businesses were created in remote Alaskan villages with the help of the Community Enterprise Development Corp. Native villagers own and manage the enterprises in their areas. The author says that the biggest challenge for these businesses is the managers? lack of expertise, while attempting to expand the customer-base among minority groups. The author believes the best strategy for successfully managing these enterprises is to develop a participative, non-direct, relationship with customers.
